                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Position yourself at bottom of hill behind druid stones.  Move to left so that left druid is closer to you.  This way you should be able to start the fight by clicking on the right druid (with cursor), then change your target to left one by hitting your target key.  I customized my keyboard, so I'm not sure what key that is on a non-modified keyboard.<br /><br />Now click on right druid and send in pet.  Both druids will attack pet.  Hit target key and fear left druid.  He will run off, at full speed, toward the Kithicor zone.  While he is gone, you now have time to snare, fear and dot druid that is fighting your pet.<br /><br />Now turn around and watch for the feared druid to return.  He will either come from the same direction he left or will come from behind you.  Just re-fear him until the other is dead.<br /><br />On the first pull, I normally kept the left druid feared for a minute or two so my 2 mobs were spaced out nicely.  Then enjoy the cash and fun of having a crowd watch you as you do something they all wish they could do =)</span id="msg"></font></td>
                    </tr>
